    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the complete plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Stepper Compound Component\n\n### What gets created (4 touches, 0 existing files modified)\n\n| Action | File |\n|--------|------|\n| **Create** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` |\n| **Create** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` |\n| **Append entry** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` |\n| **Append entry** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` |\n\n---\n\n### `stepper.tsx` — 8 sub-components + 1 exported hook\n\n| Export | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `Stepper` | Root `<div>` + Provider. Supports controlled (`step`/`onStepChange`) and uncontrolled (`defaultStep`) — mirrors `SidebarProvider` pattern. |\n| `StepperList` | `<div role=\"tablist\">` wrapper for the step indicators row. |\n| `StepperItem` | Per-step wrapper; reads `activeStep` from context to compute `data-state=\"active|completed|inactive\"`. Sets a secondary `StepperItemContext`. |\n| `StepperTrigger` | Clickable `<button role=\"tab\">` circle. Shows `<CheckIcon>` when completed, step number otherwise. |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` for the step label; dims via `data-[state=inactive]:text-muted-foreground`. |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` for the sub-label. |\n| `StepperSeparator` | Divider `<div>` that colors primary when the enclosing item is completed — pure CSS via `group-data-[state=completed]/stepper-item:bg-primary`. |\n| `StepperPanel` | Content panel `<div role=\"tabpanel\">` hidden via `data-[state=inactive]:hidden`. |\n| `useStepper` | Exported hook for accessing stepper state from any descendant. |\n\n### Architecture highlights\n- **Dual context** — root `StepperContext` + per-item `StepperItemContext` (same pattern as `ToggleGroup` → `ToggleGroupItem`)\n- **No Radix primitive** — pure HTML elements with manual ARIA (`role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `role=\"tabpanel\"`, `aria-selected`, `aria-current=\"step\"`)\n- **No new npm dependencies** — only `lucide-react` (already a registry-style dep) and `@/lib/utils`\n- **All state expressed via `data-state`** — Tailwind `data-[...]` variants handle all visual changes, no JS class manipulation\n\n### Registry entries\n- `ui/_registry.ts`: `{ name: \"stepper\", type: \"registry:ui\", dependencies: [\"lucide-react\"], files: [...] }`\n- `examples/_registry.ts`: `{ name: \"stepper-demo\", type: \"registry:example\", registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"], files: [...] }`",
